---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research"
  description="Publications and research projects in reinforcement learning and machine learning."
>
  <header style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">
      Research Roadmap &amp; Interests
    </p>
    <h1>Future Horizons &amp; Research Directions</h1>
    <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary); max-width: 40rem; margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7;">
      My academic pursuit lies at the intersection of rigorous statistical inference and high-performance machine learning, with a particular focus on the following domains:
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="research-cards-container">
    <!-- Direction 1: Bayesian RL & Distributional Optimisation -->
    <div class="research-card">
      <h3>Bayesian RL &amp; Distributional Optimisation</h3>
      <div class="research-card__tags">
        <span class="tag">Variational Inference</span>
        <span class="tag">Posterior Approximation</span>
        <span class="tag">Epistemic Uncertainty</span>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Inline SVG for Bayesian RL -->
      <div class="diagram-wrapper bayesian-diagram">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 600 250" width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <defs>
            <linearGradient id="distGrad" x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="1">
              <stop offset="0%" stop-color="#A3B899" stop-opacity="0.6"/>
              <stop offset="100%" stop-color="#A3B899" stop-opacity="0"/>
            </linearGradient>
          </defs>
          <line x1="50" y1="200" x2="550" y2="200" stroke="var(--color-border)" stroke-width="2" />
          
          <path class="glow-path" d="M 100 200 C 150 200, 150 100, 200 100 C 250 100, 250 200, 300 200" fill="url(#distGrad)" stroke="#A3B899" stroke-width="2" />
          <path class="glow-path-dashed" d="M 200 200 C 260 200, 260 50, 320 50 C 380 50, 380 200, 440 200" fill="url(#distGrad)" stroke="#A3B899" stroke-width="3" stroke-dasharray="6 4" />
          <path class="glow-path" d="M 350 200 C 390 200, 390 120, 430 120 C 470 120, 470 200, 510 200" fill="url(#distGrad)" stroke="#A3B899" stroke-width="2" />

          <text x="180" y="150" font-size="22" text-anchor="middle" style="opacity: 0.8;">🎲</text>
          <text x="400" y="130" font-size="22" text-anchor="middle" style="opacity: 0.8;">🎲</text>

          <circle class="glow-circle" cx="320" cy="50" r="6" fill="var(--color-bg)" stroke="var(--color-text-primary)" stroke-width="3" />
          <circle cx="320" cy="50" r="12" fill="none" stroke="#D6CBBF" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.8" />
          
          <line x1="320" y1="62" x2="320" y2="200" stroke="var(--color-text-primary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 4" />
          
          <text x="350" y="55" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)">Thompson Sample (Optimum)</text>
          <text x="320" y="56" font-size="24" text-anchor="middle">🎯</text>
          <text x="320" y="20" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="12" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">Navigating Epistemic Uncertainty</text>
          
          <text x="200" y="225" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="13" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">Policy A</text>
          <text x="320" y="225" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="14" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" font-weight="bold" text-anchor="middle">Policy B</text>
          <text x="430" y="225" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="13" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">Policy C</text>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <p>
        Interrogating the convergence of Bayesian statistics and reinforcement learning to maximise sample efficiency within high-dimensional state spaces. By transitioning beyond conventional point estimation, I am investigating the structural guarantees of uncertainty estimation. This entails leveraging variational inference for robust posterior approximation and quantifying epistemic uncertainty within a Variational Actor-Critic framework.
      </p>
      <div class="research-card__diagram-link">
        <strong>Symbolic Nexus:</strong> This trajectory sits firmly at the intersection of Stats and RL, bridging rigorous statistical probability with dynamic environment navigation.
      </div>
      <div class="research-card__challenge">
        Challenge: Balancing Sample Efficiency with Computational Complexity in High-dimensional Stochastic Environments.
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Direction 2: Privacy-Preserving Offline RL -->
    <div class="research-card">
      <h3>Privacy-Preserving Offline RL</h3>
      <div class="research-card__tags">
        <span class="tag">Differential Privacy</span>
        <span class="tag">Machine Unlearning</span>
        <span class="tag">Optimisation under Constraints</span>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Inline SVG for Privacy RL -->
      <div class="diagram-wrapper privacy-diagram">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 600 250" width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <g transform="translate(100, 150)">
            <circle class="glow-node" cx="-30" cy="10" r="10" fill="var(--color-border)" />
            <circle class="glow-node" cx="20" cy="-20" r="14" fill="var(--color-border)" />
            <circle class="glow-node" cx="80" cy="5" r="12" fill="var(--color-border)" />
            <circle class="glow-node" cx="130" cy="-15" r="16" fill="var(--color-border)" />
            <circle class="glow-node" cx="180" cy="20" r="11" fill="var(--color-border)" />
            <circle class="glow-node" cx="230" cy="-5" r="13" fill="var(--color-border)" />
          </g>

          <path class="glow-shield" d="M 200 40 C 330 40, 360 110, 200 230 C 40 110, 70 40, 200 40 Z" fill="#D6CBBF" fill-opacity="0.15" stroke="#D6CBBF" stroke-width="4" stroke-linejoin="round" />
          
          <text x="200" y="80" font-size="30" text-anchor="middle">🛡️</text>
          <text x="200" y="110" font-family="var(--font-mono)" font-size="16" font-weight="bold" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">(ε, δ)-DP Guarantee</text>
          <text x="200" y="130" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="12" fill="var(--color-text-secondary)" text-anchor="middle">Utility-Optimised Boundary</text>

          <g transform="translate(420, 80)">
            <path d="M 0 0 C 0 -15, 70 -15, 70 0 L 70 70 C 70 85, 0 85, 0 70 Z" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-text-secondary)" stroke-width="2" />
            <path d="M 0 0 C 0 15, 70 15, 70 0" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-text-secondary)" stroke-width="2" />
            <path d="M 0 35 C 0 50, 70 50, 70 35" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-text-secondary)" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 4" />
            
            <text x="35" y="10" font-size="26" text-anchor="middle">🔐</text>
            
            <line class="glow-accent" x1="15" y1="30" x2="55" y2="70" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round" />
            <line class="glow-accent" x1="55" y1="30" x2="15" y2="70" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round" />
            
            <text x="35" y="105" font-family="var(--font-sans)" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="var(--color-text-primary)" text-anchor="middle">Provable Unlearning</text>
          </g>
          
          <path class="glow-arrow" d="M 320 135 C 360 135, 380 115, 405 115" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-border-light)" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arrow)" stroke-dasharray="4 4" />
          
          <defs>
            <marker id="arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
              <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="var(--color-border-light)" />
            </marker>
          </defs>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <p>
        Exploring the structural guarantees of $(\epsilon, \delta)$-Differential Privacy within offline reinforcement learning, particularly concerning sensitive medical and financial logs. Rather than relying on naive noise injection, the objective is to architect utility-optimised mechanisms that negotiate the privacy-utility trade-off via precise optimisation under constraints. This encompasses integrating machine unlearning for efficient policy updates and ensuring robust policy evaluation under stringent privacy boundaries.
      </p>
      <div class="research-card__diagram-link">
        <strong>Symbolic Nexus:</strong> This pursuit demands a seamless integration across all three vertices of the trilemma (CS × Stats × RL), embedding systemic privacy constraints directly into statistical and sequential decision domains.
      </div>
      <div class="research-card__challenge">
        Challenge: Architecting Utility-Optimised Mechanisms without Compromising $(\epsilon, \delta)$-Differential Privacy Guarantees.
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Direction 3: Applied Research / Industrial Collaboration -->
    <div class="research-card">
      <h3>Applied Research: LLM-as-a-judge Evaluation</h3>
      <div class="research-card__tags">
        <span class="tag">Industrial Collaboration</span>
        <span class="tag">Gemini 2.5</span>
        <span class="tag">Rigorous Evaluation</span>
      </div>
      
      <p>
        As an extension of exploring uncertainty and rigorous model evaluation, I orchestrated a Capstone project in direct collaboration with <strong><a href="https://episod.ink/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Episod</a></strong>, a commercial service. This involved engineering an <em>LLM-as-a-judge</em> framework utilising the Gemini 2.5 architecture to establish rigorous evaluation metrics for their production system. The project entailed designing 110 meticulously crafted test cases to quantify performance boundaries and ensure objective assessment. <em>(Note: Source code is maintained in an industrial purpose private repository to comply with collaboration protocols).</em>
      </p>
      <div class="research-card__diagram-link">
        <strong>Symbolic Nexus:</strong> Bridging the gap between theoretical Bayesian foundations and practical commercial utility, demonstrating how mathematical rigour actively contributes to the evaluation logic of real-world AI services.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Research Cards Styles */
  .research-cards-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }
  
  .research-card {
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }
  
  :global(.dark) .research-card {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
  }

  .research-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 6px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }
  
  :global(.dark) .research-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 6px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
  }

  .research-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .research-card__tags {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .research-card__tags .tag {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    background-color: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .research-card p {
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .research-card__diagram-link {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .research-card__challenge {
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Inline SVG Styles */
  .diagram-wrapper {
    margin: 2rem 0;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border: 1px dashed var(--color-border);
    transition: border-color 0.3s ease;
  }
  .diagram-wrapper:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }
  
  /* Bayesian Glow */
  :global(.dark) .bayesian-diagram svg .glow-path {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(163, 184, 153, 0.4));
  }
  :global(.dark) .bayesian-diagram svg .glow-path-dashed {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px rgba(163, 184, 153, 0.6));
  }
  :global(.dark) .bayesian-diagram svg .glow-circle {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px rgba(214, 203, 191, 0.5));
  }

  /* Privacy Glow */
  :global(.dark) .privacy-diagram svg .glow-shield {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 10px rgba(214, 203, 191, 0.4));
  }
  :global(.dark) .privacy-diagram svg .glow-accent {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 8px rgba(163, 184, 153, 0.5));
  }
  :global(.dark) .privacy-diagram svg .glow-node {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2));
  }
</style>
